insertResult

public boolean insertResult(java.lang.String deviceID,
                            PingProtocolType protocol,
                            long responseTime,
                            long executionTime)
Inserts a ping result into the status_polling_history table

Parameters:
deviceID - - device id that coordinates with device objects
pingType - - type of ping performed. Used for grouping results.
responseTime - - -1 for timeout, non-negative, non-zero for successful ping. Ping tests without a round-trip time can simply use 1 to signify success or some other useful value like system up time. Otherwise, use the round-trip time in milliseconds here.
executionTime - - Date.getTime() from when ping was executed
Returns:
- code>true if 1 row was affected, false for failure
